Is the following code block parallelizable (specifically the loop iterations)?

```c
for( i=0 ; i<=10 ;i++) a[i]=x;
for (i=0; i<100 ;i++) b[i]=i ;
```

The following parallel code will give correct results as the sequential version:

```c
#pragma omp parallel for
for(i=0; i<100; i++)
  b[i] = (a[i] + b[i]) + c[i];
```

Will the following parallel code give correct results as in its sequential version:

```c
int tmp;
#pragma omp parallel for
for(i=0; i<n; i++){
  tmp = a[i];
  a[i] = b[i];
  b[i] = tmp;
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

```cpp
int m = 1;

#pragma omp parallel for reduction(+:m)
for(int j = 1; j < 5; j++)
    m = m * j;

cout << m;
```

Is it possible to parallelize the following code?
```c
for (i=0; i<100; i++) a[i] = x;
for (i=0; i<100; i++) b[i] = i;
```

Is it possible to parallelize the following loop iterations?
```c
for (i=0; i<100; i++) { 
  b[i] = i; 
  a[i] = a[i] - b[i]; 
}
```

Can the following code be parallelized?

```c
for (i = 1; i < 100; i++) {
  for (j = 1; j < 100; j++) {
    a[i][j] = a[i-1][j];
  }
}
```

Is it possible to exchange the following two loops?

```c
for (j = 1; j < n; j++) {
  for (i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    a[i][j] = a[i][j-1];
  }
}
```

Is it possible to parallelize the following code?
```c
for ( i = 0 ; i < 100 ; i++ ) a [i] = x;
for ( i = 0 ; i < 100 ; i++ ) b [i] = i;
```

Is the following code parallelizable?
```c
for (i = 1; i < n; i++) 
    a[i-1] = b[i];
```

Is it possible to parallelize the following loop iterations?

```c
for ( i = 0 ; i < 100 ; i++ ) {
  b [i] = i; 
  a [i] = a [i] - b[i]; 
}
```
